  "response": "Earthquakes mostly occur along tectonic plate boundaries, particularly in areas known as the \"Ring of Fire\" around the Pacific Ocean. This region includes countries like:\n\n1. Japan\n2. Indonesia\n3. Philippines\n4. Chile\n5. Peru\n6. United States (especially California)\n7. Alaska\n\nOther significant earthquake-prone areas include:\n\n- The Himalayan region (between India and China)\n- Mediterranean region\n- Mid-Atlantic Ridge\n- Western coast of North and South America\n- Parts of Turkey and Iran\n\nThese locations experience frequent seismic activity due to the movement and interaction of tectonic plates, where they collide, slide past, or move away from each other.",
